Classes/CLValue.html#/s:16CasperSDKInSwi.name: getCLValueWrapperDirect(from:clType:)
Classes/CLValue.html#/s:16CasperSDKInSwi.abstract: Get CLValue from Json string, with given CLType for that CLValue. The Json string is from the input with name “from”, and you have to know what CLType to parse to get the corresponding CLValue for that such CLType, retrieve from the “from” parameter

Classes/CLValue.html#/s:16CasperSDKInSwi.name: getCLValueWrapper(from:clType:keyStr:)
Classes/CLValue.html#/s:16CasperSDKInSwi.abstract: Get CLValue from Json string, with given CLType for that CLValue. The Json string is from the input with name “from”, and you have to know what CLType to parse to get the corresponding CLValue for that such CLType, retrieve from the “from” parameter

Classes/CLValue.html#/s:16CasperSDKInSwi.name: getCLValueWrapperPrimitiveFromRaw(input:clType:)
Classes/CLValue.html#/s:16CasperSDKInSwi.abstract: Get CLValue primitive from Json string, with given CLType for that CLValue. The Json string is from the input with name “from”, and you have to know what CLType to parse to get the corresponding CLValue for that such CLType, retrieve from the “from” parameter. This function deal with CLType primitive of no recursive part in side that CLType, such as Bool, String, Int

Classes/CLValue.html#/s:16CasperSDKInSwi.name: getCLValueWrapperPrimitive(from:clType:)
Classes/CLValue.html#/s:16CasperSDKInSwi.abstract: Get CLValue primitive from a parameter of type primitive (with no recursive part inside), with given CLType for that CLValue. The string is from the input with name “from”, and you have to know what CLType to parse to get the corresponding CLValue for that such CLType, retrieve from the “from” parameter. This function deal with CLType primitive of no recursive part in side that CLType, such as Bool, String, Int

Classes/CLValue.html#/s:16CasperSDKInSwi.name: getCLValueWrapperCompound(from:clType:)
Classes/CLValue.html#/s:16CasperSDKInSwi.abstract: Get CLValue from a parameter of type compound (with recursive part inside), with given CLType for that CLValue. The string is from the input with name “from”, and you have to know what CLType to parse to get the corresponding CLValue for that such CLType, retrieve from the “from” parameter. This function deal with CLType compound with recursive part in side that CLType, such as List, Map, Tuple1, Tuple2, Tuple3 …

Classes/CLValue.html#/s:16CasperSDKInSwi.name: getCLValue(from:)
Classes/CLValue.html#/s:16CasperSDKInSwi.abstract: Get CLValue with full value: bytes, parsed and cl_type. This function do the task of retrieving information of bytes,parsed and cl_type from the string map [String:Any] from the input.

Classes/CLTypeHelper.html#/s:16CasperSDK.name: jsonToCLTypePrimitive(from:keyStr:)
Classes/CLTypeHelper.html#/s:16CasperSDK.abstract: Get CLType primitive (CLType with no recursive type inside) from Json string

Classes/CLTypeHelper.html#/s:16CasperSDK.name: jsonToCLTypeCompound(from:keyStr:)
Classes/CLTypeHelper.html#/s:16CasperSDK.abstract: Get CLType compound from Json string, which are the recursive CLType such as List(CLType), Map(CLType,CLType), Tuple1(CLType), Tuple2(CLType,CLType),Tuple3(CLType,CLType,CLType)…

Classes/CLTypeHelper.html#/s:16CasperSDK.name: directJsonToCLType(from:)
Classes/CLTypeHelper.html#/s:16CasperSDK.abstract: Get CLType from Json string. If the Json string can convert to CLType primitive, then return the CLType primitive, otherwise return the CLType getting from the CLType compound

Classes/CLTypeHelper.html.name: CLTypeHelper
Classes/CLTypeHelper.html.abstract: Class for handling the conversion from Json String to CLType
